[[File:Motosumiyoshi-Jinja 002.JPG|right|thumb]] {{nihongo|'''Moto-Sumiyoshi Shrine'''|本住吉神社|Motosumiyoshi Jinja}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Higashinada-ku, Kobe|Higashinada]] ward, [[Kobe]]. It is one of the biggest shrines in western Kobe and is located next to [[Sumiyoshi Station (JR West)|Sumiyoshi Station]]. There is documentary evidence that the shrine has existed since the 13th century.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hyogo-jinjacho.com/data/6301005.html |title=本住吉神社 |access-date=10 May 2016}}</ref>
Moto-Sumiyoshi Shrine holds a [[danjiri]] festival in May each year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.city.kobe.lg.jp/ward/kuyakusho/higashinada/foreign/overview/danjiri_festival.html |title=Higashinada Ward Danjiri Festival |date=25 March 2008 |access-date=10 May 2016}}</ref> The portable shrines are wheeled through the neighborhoods around the shrine by teams of about 50 people.
